## QUERY EXECUTION PATTERNS

### Pattern 1: Simple Aggregation (2-3 dimensions)
Used in: 02_descriptive_analysis.sql
```sql
SELECT [Dimension], COUNT(*) AS Count, AVG([Metric]) AS Average
FROM table
GROUP BY [Dimension]
```

### Pattern 2: Multi-Dimensional Analysis (5-7 dimensions)
Used in: 05_business_cases.sql, 06_executive_kpis.sql
```sql
SELECT [Dim1], [Dim2], [Dim3],
       COUNT(*) AS Total,
       SUM(CASE WHEN [Flag] = 1 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Count_Subset,
       AVG([Metric1]) AS Avg1,
       AVG([Metric2]) AS Avg2
FROM table
GROUP BY [Dim1], [Dim2], [Dim3]
```

### Pattern 3: Ranking with Window Functions (Top-N per group)
Used in: 04_window_functions.sql
```sql
SELECT [Columns] FROM (
    SELECT [Columns], ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY [GroupBy] ORDER BY [OrderBy] DESC) AS rn
    FROM table
) ranked
WHERE rn = [N]
```

### Pattern 4: Conditional Business Rules (CASE-based)
Used in: 05_business_cases.sql
```sql
SELECT [Columns],
       CASE 
           WHEN [Condition1] AND [Condition2] THEN 'Category1'
           WHEN [Condition3] THEN 'Category2'
           ELSE 'Category3'
       END AS Classification
FROM table
